        <h2 class="centered-title">BULL PIPS SYSTEM</h2>
        <div class="hero-image"></div>
        <div class="product-grid">
            <div class="product">
                <p><strong>Summary:</strong></p>
                <h3>Trade Entry Points</h3>
                <h4>Buy Signals</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Price Position</strong>: Ensure the price is above the moving averages.</li>
                    <li><strong>CCI Indicator</strong>: Look for 3 or 4 blue boxes on the CCI indicator (avoid 1 or 2 boxes).</li>
                    <li><strong>Retracement Finder (RF)</strong>: Confirm an RF switch on the Retracement Finder indicator during the same candle as the CCI confirmation. This is signalled by an upward red bar.</li>
                    <li><strong>Entry Timing</strong>: Enter the trade at the close of the setup bar.</li>
                </ol>
                <h4>Sell Signals</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Price Position</strong>: Ensure the price is below the moving averages.</li>
                    <li><strong>CCI Indicator</strong>: Look for 3 or 4 red boxes on the CCI indicator (avoid 1 or 2 boxes).</li>
                    <li><strong>Retracement Finder (RF)</strong>: Confirm an RF switch on the Retracement Finder indicator during the same candle as the CCI confirmation. This is signalled by a downward red bar.</li>
                    <li><strong>Entry Timing</strong>: Enter the trade at the close of the setup bar.</li>
                </ol>
                <p><strong>Note:</strong> An RF switch occurs when the Retracement Finder histogram bar changes from positive to negative or vice versa, as highlighted in the image below. The circled bars indicate RF switches.</p>
                <h3>Re-Entry Trades</h3>
                <p>Re-enter the market to capitalize on additional opportunities within the same trend direction:</p>
                <h4>Down-Trend Re-Entry</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>CCI Indicator</strong>: From the initial entry, 3 or 4 red boxes turn to 1, 2, or 3 blue boxes, then revert back to 3 or 4 red boxes.</li>
                    <li><strong>RF Confirmation</strong>: An RF switch occurs on the same bar confirming the re-entry signal.</li>
                </ol>
                <h4>Up-Trend Re-Entry</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>CCI Indicator</strong>: From the initial entry, 3 or 4 blue boxes turn to 1, 2, or 3 red boxes, then revert back to 3 or 4 blue boxes.</li>
                    <li><strong>RF Confirmation</strong>: An RF switch occurs on the same bar confirming the re-entry signal.</li>
                </ol>
                <p>By following these rules, you can effectively identify optimal trade entry points and re-entry opportunities, maximizing your potential for profitable trades.</p>
